OL,3,CThe new Ebola virus outbreak, explained
OL,5,FThe Ebola outbreak in the Democratic
OL,6,FRepublic of Congo (DRC) and Uganda,
OL,7,Fwas declared a public health emergency
OL,8,Fby the World Health Organisation.
OL,10,FEbola is a highly contagious virus
OL,11,Fthat can be contracted via bodily
OL,12,Ffluids such as vomit, blood or semen.
OL,13,FThe disease it causes is rare, but can
OL,14,Fbe severe and often fatal.
OL,16,FIn a post on X, the World Health
OL,17,FOrganisation (WHO) said the outbreak
OL,18,Fdoes not meet the criteria of a
OL,19,Fpandemic emergency, like Covid-19, and
OL,20,Fadvised against the closure of
OL,21,Finternational borders.
